This is the README file for Object::Composite, a module that allows per 
object Composites.

Please refer to 'perldoc Object::Composite' after installation for 
details.

#####################################################################

* Description

Object::Composite

    Object::Composite allows you to build composite objects, which, behind
    the scenes redispatch their calls to other objects. This is particularly
    useful if you wish to have a unified interface to, for example, different
    databases, objects, gateways, etc.

    
#####################################################################

* Installation

Object::Composite follows the standard perl module install process

perl Makefile.PL
make
make test
make install

The module uses no C or XS parts, so no c-compiler is required.

